SIMPLE: splendid
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Splendid
<hw>Splen"did</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>splendidus</ets>, fr. <ets>splendere</ets> shine; cf. Lith.
<ets>splend⟦eum⟧ti</ets>: cf. F. <ets>splendide</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Possessing or displaying splendor; shining; very
bright; <as>as, a <ex>splendid</ex> sun</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Showy; magnificent; sumptuous; pompous; <as>as, a
<ex>splendid</ex> palace; a <ex>splendid</ex> procession or
pageant.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Illustrious; heroic; brilliant; celebrated; famous;
<as>as, a <ex>splendid</ex> victory or reputation</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Splendidious</ent>⟦br⟧
